info.name: NovelCOVID API v3 (github.com/NovelCOVID/API)
info.description:
API for Current cases and more stuff about COVID-19 or the Novel Coronavirus Strain.

- [Website](https://github.com/NovelCOVID/API)

request.description: Returns a JSON array with an element for each continent that has stats available.
Get the same data from the /v2/continents endpoint, but filter down to a specific continent.

Returns a JSON array with an element for each country that has stats available. This includes iso codes, lat/long, a link to the country flag, cases, new cases, deaths, new deaths, recovered, active cases, critical cases, and cases/deaths per one million people. Data is updated every 10 minutes.
Get the same data from the /countries endpoint, but filter down to a specific country.

variable.description: Multiple country names separated by commas

request.description: Get the same data from the /countries endpoint, but filter down to multiple specific countries. Data is updated every 10 minutes.

response.name: All GHI CSSE

request.description: Get JHU CSSE county specific data. This includes confirmed cases, deaths, recovered, and coordinates. Data is updated every 10 minutes

response.name: All US County Data

request.description: Get JHU CSSE county specific data. This includes confirmed cases, deaths, recovered, and coordinates. Returns array because there are duplicate names. Data is updated every 10 minutes.

query.description: number of days you want the data to go back to. Default is 30. Use all for full data set. Ex: 15, all, 24

request.description: Get time series info from the JHU CSSE Data Repository. Every date since 1/22/20 has an entry tracking deaths, cases, and recoveries for each country. Updated each day at 23:59 UTC. Data is updated every 10 minutes.

query.description: number of days you want the data to go back to. Default is 30. Use all for full data set. Ex: 15, all, 24
